  "why": "HDTest uses a differential (metamorphic-style) oracle that assumes mutated inputs should preserve the original semantic label and it enforces limits on perturbation magnitude relative to the original seed throughout fuzzing. The framework explicitly measures distances between each mutant and the original input (normalized L1/L2), rejects mutants that exceed a small 'invisible' threshold (e.g., L2 < 1), and guides seed selection via a similarity-based fitness computed against the original class reference HV. These design choices enforce semantic consistency (by comparing to the original prediction/reference HV) and preserve naturalness (by bounding perturbation relative to the original input) across iterations.",
